          <h2 id="overview">Kingston STR Overview</h2>
          <p>Kingston's short-term rental licensing bylaw took effect June 1, 2021, with significant updates in 2022, 2023, and most recently September 2024. The city defines a short-term rental as:</p>

          <blockquote class="bylaw-quote">
            "Short-term Rental means all or part of a Dwelling Unit used to provide sleeping accommodations for a period equal to or less than thirty (30) consecutive days in exchange for payment."
            <cite>Kingston Bylaw 2021-10, Part 1 Definitions</cite>
          </blockquote>

          <p>Note that Kingston uses <strong>30 days</strong> as the threshold, compared to Toronto's 28 days. This is a minor difference but worth knowing if you're pricing extended stays.</p>

          <div class="key-stats">
            <div class="stat-item">
